    (21,'progress_plc_comp','<p>MEAP Growth measures the percent of students in the school that increased their proficiency or maintained proficiency from one year to the next. This measure only uses those students that have taken the MEAP test at least two years in a row at a single school. This measure is built using the State’s Performance Level Change Index (PLC) data that is included in the Top-to-Bottom, but unlike the State’s PLC, we have not netted out the percentage of kids that lost proficiency from one year to the next.  The PLC and MEAP Growth results are correlated at about .98, so strong PLC = Strong MEAP Growth.</p>\r\n  <TABLE>\r\n   <TBODY>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          MEAP Growth\r\n       </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n   </TBODY>\r\n    <TBODY>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          <BR>\r\n          \r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          Floor\r\n       </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          37%\r\n       </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n   </TBODY>\r\n    <TBODY>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          <BR>\r\n          \r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          Target\r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          73%\r\n       </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n   </TBODY>\r\n    <TBODY>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          Points\r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          Min\r\n       </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          Max\r\n       </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          0\r\n       </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          18.51%\r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          38.15%\r\n        </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          1\r\n       </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          38.20%\r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          40.33%\r\n        </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          2\r\n       </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          40.36%\r\n        </TD>\r\n       <TD>\r\n          42.84%\r\n        </TD>\r\n     </TR>\r\n     <TR>\r\n        <TD>\r\n          3\r\n       </TD>\r\n     